<pb n=510><head>DIOPHANTUS OF ALEXANDRIA</head>
<I>Lemma</I> 1. If a rational right-angled triangle be formed
from <I>m, n,</I> the perpendicular sides are 2<I>mn, m</I><SUP>2</SUP> - <I>n</I><SUP>2</SUP>.
